author: Justin Hoyo
text:
Visited this gym as the Evolt body scanner machine is free to use 24/7. But the gym itself is mediocre purely because the equipment, barbell and dumbbells are very poorly maintained. The barbells are especially rusty and smelly. Benches are also worn and metals were rusty.

If I ignore the poor maintenance, this outlet actually has potential - 2 stories, good variety of equipment and wide range of dumbbells/weight plates.

The equipment is always clean and well-maintained, and there's plenty of space, so I rarely have to wait, even during peak hours. If you're looking for a gym that genuinely cares about its members' success and creates a fantastic vibe, look no further than Anytime Fitness

author: Jordan Boo
text:
I‚Äôve been a member at Anytime Fitness Serangoon Garden for a while now, and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with my experience. The gym is always clean, well-maintained, and equipped with a wide range of modern machines and free weights to suit all fitness levels.

The staff and trainers are incredibly friendly and professional ‚Äî they‚Äôre always ready to offer tips, guidance, or just a bit of motivation when you need it. I also love the welcoming atmosphere here; everyone‚Äôs focused and respectful, which makes working out enjoyable and stress-free.

Being open 24/7 is a huge plus, and the location is super convenient with plenty of parking nearby. Whether you‚Äôre a beginner or a seasoned gym-goer, Anytime Fitness Serangoon Garden is an excellent place to train, stay consistent, and be part of a supportive fitness community.

Highly recommended! üí™

author: Darren Tan
text:
I‚Äôve been to many gyms, but this one truly stands out! The facility is immaculately clean, which makes every workout so much more enjoyable. The staff is incredibly friendly and welcoming, always greeting you with a smile and ready to assist.

The gym itself is spacious and well-equipped, with two floors packed with a wide variety of high-quality equipment, so you never have to wait to use a machine. Whether you're into strength training, cardio, or functional workouts, this gym has everything you need.

A special shoutout to Eugene, the head trainer‚Äîhe‚Äôs an exceptional personal trainer who is knowledgeable, motivating, and truly cares about each client‚Äôs progress. He takes the time to ensure proper form, pushes you to achieve your goals, and brings an encouraging energy to every session.

If you're looking for a top-tier gym with great facilities, a supportive community, and outstanding trainers, this is the place to be! Highly recommend! üí™üî•

author: Jo
text:
decent equipment, although quite cramped and crowded at times.

i got an injury requiring surgery and obtained a doctor's memo for premature termination of my contract with AF serangoon gardens. initially i tried to continue gymming but my surgery recovery was being impaired by the workouts, hence my surgeon and physical therapist suggested i cease my gym activities. AF serangoon gardens was being very difficult with processing my termination, citing that they saw me previously at the gym, and various clauses in the contract despite my very valid reason for termination alongside proper documentation and doctor's letter in alignment with the contract. this was very tedious and left a very terrible impression of this gym. highly DO NOT recommend having to deal with the staff here.

author: Fujirimaz
text:
I‚Äôve been going to Anytime Fitness Serangoon Garden for a while now, and it‚Äôs been a fantastic experience overall.

The gym is located in a really convenient spot, making it easy for me to drop by before or after work. Whether you‚Äôre driving or using public transport, getting there is hassle-free, with plenty of parking available as well.

The gym is well-equipped with everything you need for a complete workout‚Äîplenty of cardio machines, free weights, and functional training areas. The equipment is modern and well-maintained, making my workouts smooth and efficient.

The staff at this location are top-notch. They‚Äôre always friendly, approachable, and eager to help. Whether I need advice on equipment or workout techniques, they‚Äôre attentive and supportive, creating a positive and welcoming environment. Shout out to my trainer, Eugene, for guiding me toward my goals and pushing me to my limits!

The gym is never overcrowded, even during peak hours. It has a relaxed and inclusive vibe, making it a comfortable place to work out, whether you‚Äôre just starting or are more experienced.

If you‚Äôre looking for a gym with great accessibility, a friendly atmosphere, and helpful staff, Anytime Fitness Serangoon Garden is a solid choice!

author: Natasha Ng
text:
I've been a member at Anytime Fitness Serangoon Garden for a while now, and I can honestly say it‚Äôs one of the best gyms around. The equipment is well-maintained, and there‚Äôs a great variety, so you never run out of options. The gym is always clean, and the 24/7 access is super convenient, especially with my busy schedule.
The staff and trainers are incredibly friendly and knowledgeable‚Äîthey make the environment welcoming and motivating. Whether you're a beginner or a regular, you'll feel right at home here. Highly recommend for anyone looking to stay fit in a great community! üí™

author: Dharshini Elangoven
text:
I am writing to express my deep disappointment and concern regarding an incident that took place during my recent visit to your gym. I was working out with my friend, who trains frequently, so that I could learn from her‚Äîespecially since I am still improving my form on certain exercises. However, during our session, a trainer named Eugene approached my friend and abruptly told her that she needed to leave the gym immediately.

He claimed to have been watching us through the surveillance cameras and assumed that my friend was a personal trainer. Instead of approaching her directly in a respectful manner to clarify the situation, he made an immediate judgment based on camera footage and proceeded to tell her off in an unprofessional and discourteous way. This interaction was not only rude but also felt unethical and completely unnecessary.

This experience has left me feeling extremely uncomfortable and hesitant about returning to the gym. I now question the level of surveillance being conducted on members while they train. What is the intent behind watching members through cameras while they work out? Should I now be worried that I am constantly being monitored and scrutinized while simply trying to improve my fitness?

I have always believed that Anytime Fitness promotes a welcoming and supportive environment, but this experience has made me feel otherwise. I urge you to address this issue and ensure that members are treated with respect rather than suspicion. I hope you take this feedback seriously, as no one should feel uncomfortable or unwelcome in a space meant for health and wellness.

I would appreciate a response regarding this matter and what steps will be taken to prevent such incidents from happening again.

author: Jaenus Lee
text: I've been hitting up this gym for almost a year now, and it's been pretty solid. Its convenient accessibility and diverse array of equipment make it a perfect fit for individuals at every fitness level. Plus, the staffs are usually nice and approachable! It's a welcoming atmosphere, perfect for anyone looking to improve their health and fitness. If you're looking for a no-nonsense gym that delivers, this is it!

author: Van Cliff
text:
We came to visit this AF branch an hours ago because me and my friend plan to have a good brunch around the area. Unfortunately we were treated as if we trespass or came to the gym drunk and make noise. This unbelievable behaviour of whom they called ‚Äúclub MANAGER‚Äù approach us in a very rude manner and said ‚Äúyou have to leave the gym‚Äù. I‚Äôm like why? Then he showed me his cctv showing me stopping my set and told me ‚Äúyou‚Äôre a trainer‚Äù
If I look like a trainer than you then that‚Äôs a compliment but it would be great if next time you learn and apply to approach things like this in a professional way.
I am a professional IFBB bodybuilder. If I want to train my clients, I‚Äôll train them in my own gym because I have my own one.  I came to train with my friend who needs a push and guide into a gym and go for a brunch after. If going to a gym looking fit more than your own trainers is a problem then you have a very toxic fitness environment for public. You shouldn‚Äôt allow people enter your gym as looking fit makes you look like a trainer.

It‚Äôs a shame that a person (head trainer Eugene) who conducting client kept looking at the phone monitoring us on cctv what were doing. In front of our eyes his client came without warm up and cool down, session finished in 30mins just doing a cable row. What a pitiful experience for those innocent people who got daylight rubbery by this kind of trainers (head trainer) take note!
My friend who‚Äôs considering to take a PT here as she lived nearby changed her mind because of what we have witnessed.

They banned me just like that base on his inferiority. But you don‚Äôt have to take an effort to ban me actually. because I will never want to see your face again. Focus on your job Mr. Manager aka head trainer. You‚Äôre lacking your professionalism as a ‚ÄúMANAGER‚Äù and even as a ‚ÄúTRAINER‚Äù. It‚Äôs 0%.
Shame on you.

author: Darren Beck
text:
Pros: Good location and perhaps one of the better gym setups in the northeast area. There is a good selection of machines and free weights, they are well maintained, albeit some signs of wear and rust are evident. One could easily get a full body workout should he/she wishes to. Early mornings and afternoons are the best times to visit.

Cons: It is a small gym and it gets really, really, really crowded during peak hours, a crowd management system could be of use. There is also a growing clique of youngsters who seem more obsessed with filming TikTok videos of their deadlifts/squats, hogging the weights and proving their masculinity to their friends. This creates an uncomfortable environment for other members, staff seem nonchalant in addressing this and at times, involved with their antics.
